{"title":"Families","pageid":7260,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" width=\"80%\" style=\"border: 1px solid #aaa; margin: 0 auto; display: block;\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td width=\"10px\" style=\"background: #f4C340;\">\n</td>\n<td style=\"padding: 0 0 0 5px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Pen.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Pen.png\" src=\"/wiki/images/4/4f/Pen.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" data-file-width=\"32\" data-file-height=\"32\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td style=\"padding: 10px 0 10px 5px;\"><font size=\"3\"><b>This page needs revising!</b></font>\n<p><font size=\"1\">The following page is out of date and/or needs to be revised. If the page's guide needs revision, <a href=\"/wiki/Guide_to_contributing_to_the_wiki#Guide_to_Writing_and_Revising_a_Guide\" title=\"Guide to contributing to the wiki\">see here for an example</a>.</font><br />The revision reason is: <b>\"Most of the super out of date stuff from the last version has been removed, but more info on individual families and the cellphone (perhaps a whole rewrite of this page) are needed.\"</b>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td bgcolor=\"black\" align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\"><font color=\"white\"><b>FAMILIES STAFF</b></font>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"150\" align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#A68064\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:PowderGanger.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"PowderGanger.png\" src=\"/wiki/images/2/28/PowderGanger.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" data-file-width=\"32\" data-file-height=\"32\" /></a> <br /> <b>Family Member</b>\n</td>\n<td><b>Access:</b> Whatever your job is<br /> <b><a href=\"/wiki/Terminology#Additional_Access\" title=\"Terminology\"> Additional Access</a>:</b> Any place you or your family members have access to.<br /><b>Difficulty:</b> Hard<br /><b>Supervisors:</b> Nobody<br /><b>Duties:</b> Convince people to join your family, wear your uniform, tag turf for the family<br /><b>Guides:</b> This is the guide <br /><b>Quote:</b> <i>TUNNEL SNAKES RULE! We're the Tunnel Snakes! That's us, and we rule!</i>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><br />\n</p><p>Families is a gamemode based off of Goonstation's Gang mode.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Isn.27t_this_just_Gang_War.3F\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Isn't this just Gang War?</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Tunnel_Snakes_Rule.21\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Tunnel Snakes Rule!</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Getting_recruited\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Getting recruited</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#The_important_stuff\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The important stuff</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#The_Objective\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Objective</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Equipment\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Equipment</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Recruiting_more_members\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recruiting more members</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#This_family_SUCKS_and_ISN.27T_THE_TUNNEL_SNAKES.21\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">This family SUCKS and ISN'T THE TUNNEL SNAKES!</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Station_Staff\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Station Staff</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-3 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Caught_in_the_Crossfire\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Caught in the Crossfire</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span id=\"Isn't_this_just_Gang_War?\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Isn.27t_this_just_Gang_War.3F\">Isn't this just Gang War?</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Isn&#039;t this just Gang War?\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Isn&#039;t this just Gang War?\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Nope! Gang War was removed a long time ago. This is a different gamemode. Notably, you can't spawn any weaponry, and joining a Family is 100% voluntary.\n</p>\n<h1><span id=\"Tunnel_Snakes_Rule!\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Tunnel_Snakes_Rule.21\">Tunnel Snakes Rule!</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Tunnel Snakes Rule!\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Tunnel Snakes Rule!\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In this mode, two to three(or 11, if the admins will it to be) criminal families spawn on the station. Their goal is to accomplish their family's objective. These objectives are unique to family and usually have the family engage in some kind of conflict with either a department on the station, station security or other families. Unlike most other antagonists there isn't a hard win/lose condition, and the family goal is merely an overarching theme that the family follows.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Getting_recruited\">Getting recruited</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Getting recruited\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Getting recruited\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>All it takes to join a gang is to ask an already-converted member to recruit you. Once you have your uniform, cellphone and spraypaint, you're a gangster! \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_important_stuff\">The important stuff</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: The important stuff\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: The important stuff\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Objective\">The Objective</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: The Objective\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: The Objective\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The objective you get is based on your Family's randomly chosen theme! The available themes are the Grove Street Families, the Ballas, the Los Santos Vagos, the San Fierro Triad, the Russian Mafia, the Italian Mob, the Jack Bros, Dutch van der Linde's Gang, the Tojo Clan, the Monarch Henchmen, and the Tunnel Snakes(THEY RULE!).\n</p><p>Make sure to read your objective and work with the rest of the family towards this goal. Some objectives require team work to pull off, so communicate with your fellow Family members.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Equipment\">Equipment</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Equipment\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Equipment\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When joining a Family, you're given two important things!\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<table style=\"border:1px solid #A68064;\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td align=\"center\" width=\"150\" style=\"background-color:#A68064\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Gscans.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"Spray Can\"><img alt=\"Spray Can\" src=\"/wiki/images/3/3a/Gscans.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" data-file-width=\"32\" data-file-height=\"32\" /></a><br /><b>Spray Can</b>\n</td>\n<td><b>Found in: </b>Autolathes, joining a Family<br /><b>Used for:</b> Claiming turf for your Family.<br />\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background-color:#A68064;\"><b>Description</b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>These spraycans are specially modified to mark a territory for your Family. They can be used on floors and walls.\n<p>They cannot be used to tag areas that already has a gang tag in it, unless you spray directly on top of the old one. Normal crew (such as the Janitor) can clean tags.\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table style=\"border:1px solid #A68064;\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td align=\"center\" width=\"150\" style=\"background-color:#A68064\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Suit.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"Family Uniform\"><img alt=\"Family Uniform\" src=\"/wiki/images/a/ab/Suit.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" data-file-width=\"32\" data-file-height=\"32\" /></a><br /><b>Family Uniform</b>\n</td>\n<td><b>Found in: </b>Joining a Family<br /><b>Used for:</b> Repping your Family!<br />\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background-color:#A68064;\"><b>Description</b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>You get a set when you join the Family! It spawns with the complimentary spray can and cellphone. Wear this! It helps your fellow gangsters identify you. Make sure to wear your Uniform!\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recruiting_more_members\">Recruiting more members</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Recruiting more members\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Recruiting more members\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>That's easy! Simply hit the <b>secret handshake</b> button in the top left. It'll give a little prompt to anyone standing next to you that allows someone to willingly join the Family if they use it. Joining a Family is <b>voluntary, so be nice to people if you want them to join.</b> If you're told you can't recruit more members, don't worry! This is an autobalancing feature. Simply wait for the other Families to recruit more people.\n</p>\n<h3><span id=\"This_family_SUCKS_and_ISN'T_THE_TUNNEL_SNAKES!\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"This_family_SUCKS_and_ISN.27T_THE_TUNNEL_SNAKES.21\">This family SUCKS and ISN'T THE TUNNEL SNAKES!</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: This family SUCKS and ISN&#039;T THE TUNNEL SNAKES!\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: This family SUCKS and ISN&#039;T THE TUNNEL SNAKES!\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>If you tire of your current family, you can join a different family at any time! Just ditch your old uniform and go ask a rival family member if they'll let you join their family instead. They'll probably say yes! Just remember, <b>people don't really like turncoats if they find out you're one.</b> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Station_Staff\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Hudcentcom.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Hudcentcom.png\" src=\"/wiki/images/5/50/Hudcentcom.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" data-file-width=\"8\" data-file-height=\"8\" /></a> Station Staff</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Station Staff\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Station Staff\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Caught_in_the_Crossfire\">Caught in the Crossfire</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Caught in the Crossfire\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=Families&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Caught in the Crossfire\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>As a loyal employee of Nanotrasen, it is best to keep doing your job. However, if you want to join the family action, you can simply request that a Family member induct you at any time. They'll hook you up, probably. But remember, <b>once you're in the life, you're in for good.</b> You can't quit being a family member, only switching what family you're in.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240421000525\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.052 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.066 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 254/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 9842/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 2920/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   31.437      1 -tota